⚠️ CRITICAL: FOLDER STRUCTURE RULES (THE MAP) You must strictly follow this directory structure. Do not create folders like components or hooks at the root.

src/app/: Global wiring (Providers, Router, Global Styles).

src/processes/: Complex multi-step flows (e.g., audit-execution-wizard).

src/pages/: Route views. They barely contain logic; they just compose Widgets and Features.

src/widgets/: Large, standalone UI blocks (e.g., Sidebar, Header, RiskMatrixTable).

src/features/: User interactions (e.g., risk-scoring, finding-review).

src/entities/: Business Data Models & Logic (e.g., risk, audit, user). (The Brain)

src/shared/: Reusable primitives (e.g., ui/, api/, lib/, stores/). (The Kernel)

UNIDIRECTIONAL FLOW: Pages -> Widgets -> Features -> Entities -> Shared. Lower layers NEVER import from upper layers.